PT \u2014Repub-\nAviation Corp. announced today it\nhad leased front the War Assets ad\nministration for five years, with op\ntion to buy. the entire government\nowned aircraft plant facilities and\nport at Farmingdale. X. Y\u201e It was\nannounced todn>.\nThe agreement covers more than\n30 buildings, with a floor area of ap\nproximately T. 400.000 square feet,\nerected b> the government r or the\nwartime mass production of P-41\nThunderbolt fighter planes, and the\n260-acre airport with operation build\nings. paved runways and taxi strips.\nThe Farmingdale plant was Repub\nlic's main plant during the war yean\nand will continue to he for peacetime\nproduction the company said.\nRadio Production Gains\nWashington. June 20\u2014 fAP)\u2014Tbo\ncensus bureau reported today 916.701\nradio sets were produced in March,\n27 per cent more than in February\nand about 90 per cent of the average\nmonthly output in 1941. The output\nincluded 636.570 home radios, exclu\nsive of radio-phonograph combina\ntions and battery sets, which was 151\nper cent above February and 1? per\ntent higher than the 1941 average\nmonthly production.\nSuoray Oil Taro.\nA reg airat on statement for S2ft\nof 20-year debenture*, due 1366. and j.Oftft.-\n000 ahaves of par value oomnmti otoelC\nwas l today with the Securities vixi\nKicchang* com miss on by Sunday Oi! Corp.\nr>f TuUa. Okl. The aecurttie* w of\nfered THjWlciv by underwriters 'eadoff b/\nibxauuaa* Di lioa 4 C\u00ab.\u00ab Nt*\n13","height":"25893","width":"19243"}}
